he chair seat with 12 inches 305cm being a spacious allowance.";i:1;s:67:"This allows guests to comfortably cross their legs under the table.";i:2;s:58:"If you are measuring a desk chair read our office article.";i:3;s:48:"How much space between your chair and the table.";i:4;s:99:"For optimal leg room allow 10-12 inches between the seat of your chair and your underside tabletop.";i:5;s:111:"For armchairs be sure to leave to leave at least six inches between the armrest and the underside of the table.";i:6;s:158:"Ignoring everything else for the moment the realistic minimum distance between the chair seat and table top is around 24cm with the maximum being around 30cm.";i:7;s:25:"The ideal is around 26cm.";i:8;s:103:"Most modern chairs have their seat height set at around 50cm from the floor and most dining tables are.";i:9;s:55:"18 from the edge of the table to the back of the chair.";i:10;s:51:"This allows for one seated person facing the table.";i:11;s:23:"16 from chair to chair.";i:12;s:27:"Dont forget your neighbors.";i:13;s:70:"The room side-to-side is just as important perhaps more than front to.";i:14;s:48:"Distance between a dining table and an entrance.";i:15;s:105:"Provide around 48 between the table and an entrance to allow people to enter and exit the room with ease.";i:16;s:55:"Vertical space between a dining chair and dining table.";i:17;s:72:"Chairs and chair arms should be able to slide under the table with ease.";i:18;s:68:"A husky man on the other hand will need at least 44 inches of space.";i:19;s:74:"Someone in a wheelchair will need 54 inches for proper access and comfort.";i:20;s:40:"Regardless of table shape -- round oval.";i:21;s:207:"To avoid the unnatural curvature of the spine or the tensing of the neck and the shoulders the table should be so high that the elbows and underarms lie straight on the table with loosely hanging upper arms.";i:22;s:136:"An office chair with a forwardly inclined seat and simultaneous backrest support ensure that the spine is in its natural double S shape.";i:23;s:83:"The current restaurant design modules place the tables on average 12 or less apart.";i:24;s:99:"This setting however despite being preferred by restaurant owners is less desired by their patrons.";i:25;s:145:"One possible middle-ground between those two conflicting desires is the ability to make small restaurant furniture and layout changes on the fly.";i:26;s:118:"The picture to the right illustrates the minimum spacing needed for rows of tables when a service aisle is not needed.";i:27;s:23:"52 from table to table.";i:28;s:23:"18 is allowed for each.";i:29;s:315:"22 distance between chairs 19 measure from one table 19 measure from the next table-----60 accessways between tables Example 4 Provided for illustration purposes only and not to scale or designed for any specific room Exit Exit Stage All aisle accessways have a minimum of 60 inches between tables in this scenario.";i:30;s:60:"19 from each table plus the required 22 inch wide accessway.";i:31;s:54:"Distance between edge of dining table and edge of rug.";i:32;s:69:"Theres nothing worse than chair legs catching on the edge of the rug.";i:33;s:120:"This is the minimum amount of space that will accommodate chairs to sit on the rug even when pulled away from the table.";i:34;s:178:"Office Desks According to British Standard BS5588 fire regulations state that the minimum desk distance between desks should be a minimum of 60 cm and 90 cm for wheelchair users.";i:35;s:138:"However usually the space between desks is greater for practical reasons so the distance between office desks is usually closer to 100 cm.";i:36;s:102:"Just be sure that all tables have at least five feet of space between them for seating and aisle ways.";i:37;s:125:"In general any seat at a table requires 18 of depth for the chair and seating person with the service aisle extending for 24.";i:38;s:68:"Standin Lets say your party has upgraded to a swanky cocktail party.";i:39;s:162:"The general rule for tables in early care and education classrooms is the space between the seat of the chair and the underside of the table should be 7-8 inches.";i:40;s:177:"Thats just the right amount of space for children to be able to fit their legs under the table and it also ensures that the table is low enough for children to comfortably rest.";i:41;s:60:"How much space do you REALLY need between tables and chairs.";i:42;s:24:"Lakes Region Tent Event.";i:43;s:137:"Use these guidelines on proper table and chair spacing to make sure your chairs and tables seat people comfortably and with room to move.";i:44;s:43:"Chair Table Spacing Tips Suggestions 14 sq.";i:45;s:75:"Ft per person for spacious dining allows for a table chair and aisle 12 sq.";i:46;s:62:"Ft per person for cafeteria or restaurant-style seating 10 sq.";i:47;s:77:"Ft per person for banquet institutional or close seating Allow 18 inches for.";i:48;s:96:"However if the distance exceeds 36 inches it will create an awkward and conservative atmosphere.";i:49;s:75:"To provide guests with food you need enough space to walk around the table.";i:50;s:66:"Diners also need enough space to push the chair back after a meal.";i:51;s:88:"Leave a distance of at least 3 feet between the edge of the table and the wall or alley.";i:52;s:77:"Given a table of x height the chair seat should be approximately x-12 inches.";i:53;s:85:"I would not go with a smaller distance but one or maybe two inches lower would be OK.";i:54;s:74:"Leave 7 inches between the chair arm and the bottom or apron of the table.";i:55;s:52:"Provide each guest 24-30 inches at the dining table.";i:56;s:119:"To ensure adequate eating room for friends and family members alike follow the guidelines that interior decorators use.";i:57;s:110:"Distance Between Chairs Allow at least 24 inches between chairs as measured from the center point of the seat.";i:58;s:115:"For example if each seat is 18 inches wide a minimum of 6 inches between chairs will provide sufficient elbow room.";i:59;s:113:"Avoid banged up walls and keep diners comfortable by leaving at least two feet between a dining chair and a wall.";i:60;s:66:"That will allow enough room to walk behind and pull out the chair.";i:61;s:45:"Chairs should be spaced about two feet apart.";i:62;s:52:"When space allows place the dining table about four.";i:63;s:127:"A standard dining chair seat is 18 inches tall making the distance between the top of the chair and top of the table 12 inches.";i:64;s:64:"Depending on the thickness of the table or presence of an apron.";i:65;s:105:"This includes the spacing between the chairs to allow customers to get in and out and to sit comfortably.";i:66;s:97:"The type of restaurant you have is another important aspect to consider when choosing the tables.";i:67;s:82:"For full course meals a 30 x 30 table will comfortably serve only 2 seated people.";}}